 By acting on Eq.
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:first order equation"

\end_inset

 with these left eigenvectors, we obtain a 
\begin_inset Formula $4\times4$
\end_inset

 
\emph on
linear 
\emph default
eigenvalue problem for the eigenvalue 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma_{1}$
\end_inset

